5
Number of Tables

Key Observations

  • The Products table stores information about the fitness products sold, including ID, name, type, brand, price, and stock quantity.
  • The SaleDetails table tracks individual items within each sale, linking to Products and Sales tables with quantity and unit price.
  • The ServiceTickets table manages customer service requests, referencing Customers and Products with details like ticket date, issue description and status.
  • The Sales table records sales transactions, linking to the Customers table and storing sale date, total amount, and salesperson ID.
  • The Customers table stores customer details, including personal information, contact details, address, and registration date.
